{{Quote|I worked in his shadow for the sake of my career&hellip;No longer! Today the Rebel escape will be stopped&hellip;The Rebellion crushed by me! Alone!|Griff about his career under [[Anakin Skywalker/Legends|Darth Vader]] at the [[Yavin blockade|Blockade of Yavin]]|<ref name="Race for Survival">"[[Race for Survival]]"</ref>}}
'''Amise Griff''' was a [[Human/Legends|Human]] [[Gender/Legends|male]] [[Admiral/Legends|admiral]] of the [[Imperial Navy/Legends|Imperial Navy]] who commanded the [[Sector Group/Legends|Sector Group]] in the [[Bright Jewel Oversector/Legends|Bright Jewel Oversector]] and oversaw the development and construction of the [[Executor-class Star Dreadnought/Legends|''Executor''-class Star Dreadnought]] at [[Fondor/Legends|Fondor]]. Following the [[DS-1 Orbital Battle Station/Legends|Death Star]]'s destruction, Admiral Griff was removed from [[Grand Moff/Legends|Grand Moff]] [[Nox Vellam]]'s staff and handpicked by the [[Supreme Commander (Galactic Empire)/Legends|Supreme Commander]], [[Anakin Skywalker/Legends|Darth Vader]], to serve as his [[Adjutant/Legends|adjutant]].

At the [[Sith Lord/Legends|Sith Lord]]'s behest, he infiltrated a group of traitorous [[Imperial officer/Legends|Imperial officers]] who [[Mission to Fondor (Galactic Civil War)|plotted]] to hand ''[[Executor]]''<nowiki/>'s schematics over to the [[Alliance to Restore the Republic/Legends|Rebel Alliance]]. Griff arranged a meeting between them and their Rebel contact, [[Luke Skywalker/Legends|Luke Skywalker]], in hopes of delivering them all to [[Darth/Legends|Darth]] Vader. Though the turncoats were apprehended, the young [[Jedi/Legends|Jedi]] was alerted to the presence of the [[Dark Lord of the Sith/Legends|Dark Lord of the Sith]] and escaped the Admiral. After his mission on Fondor, Vader placed Griff in charge of the [[Yavin blockade|Blockade of Yavin]]. Unaware of his superior's plans, Griff resolved to step out of Vader's shadow and crush the Alliance on his own. In a desperate attempt to pursue the Rebels, the Admiral made a [[Hyperspace/Legends|hyperspace]] jump and dropped right into the [[Sith/Legends|Sith]] [[Lord/Legends|Lord]]'s [[Flagship/Legends|flagship]], which had lied in wait at this precise spot. Griff died in the subsequent collision. 

==Biography==
The [[Commanding officer/Legends|commanding officer]] of the Sector Group in the Bright Jewel Oversector, Amise Griff held the [[Imperial Navy/Legends|naval]] [[Military rank/Legends|rank]] of Admiral and answered to the local [[Grand Moff/Legends|Grand Moff]], [[Governor-General/Legends|Governor-General]] [[Nox Vellam]]. Following the disastrous [[Battle of Yavin/Legends|Battle of Yavin]] that saw the Death Star [[Battle station/Legends|battle station's]] destruction, he found himself reassigned to act as an adjutant to [[Anakin Skywalker/Legends|Darth Vader]], the [[Supreme Commander (Galactic Empire)/Legends|Commander of the Imperial Fleet]].<ref name="kenner">{{KennerCite|set=Star Wars: Shadows of the Empire (toy line)|pack=Darth Vader vs. Prince Xizor|link=soteKxizor-vader.asp}}</ref>

[[File:Admirals_plot.jpg|thumb|left|209x209px|Imperial [[Admiral/Legends|admirals]] [[Mission to Fondor (Galactic Civil War)|plot]].]]
At first, Griff served as an agent provocateur on Fondor, a role in which he proved successful; he infiltrated a cell of traitorous Imperial officers with part in the ''Executor''{{'s}} construction, regularly reporting on them to Vader. The turncoats had grown jealous of [[Lord/Legends|Lord]] Vader's unique position in the naval hierarchy as the [[Sith apprentice/Legends|right-hand]] of [[Galactic Emperor/Legends|Emperor]] [[Palpatine/Legends|Palpatine]]. Though they were not very sympathetically inclined towards the [[Alliance to Restore the Republic/Legends|Rebels]], they hoped selling the [[Executor-class Star Dreadnought/Legends|''Executor''-class Star Dreadnaught]]'s schematics to them would weaken their rival. By feigning sympathy for the traitors' cause and organizing their operations successfully, Griff eventually became their leader.

Griff was ready to arrest them when [[Luke Skywalker/Legends|Luke Skywalker]], their Rebel contact, [[Mission to Fondor (Galactic Civil War)|arrived]], and Vader ordered his capture. Griff then befriended Skywalker and helped him in his mission, still posing as a Rebel sympathizer. After some time, he formed a new plan: to organize a meeting between Skywalker and the conspirators to incriminate them and set up a trap for the Rebel hero. However, Vader insisted on personally supervising the operation, and Skywalker felt his powerful [[Dark side of the Force/Legends|dark]] presence through [[The Force/Legends|the Force]]. Although Griff's [[Stormtrooper/Legends|stormtroopers]] managed to arrest the traitors, the now-alerted young [[Jedi/Legends|Jedi]] escaped, bringing the schematics with him.

Later, Griff was placed in charge of the [[Yavin blockade|Blockade of Yavin]]. This long, drawn-out operation was marked by rivalry between Vader's supporters and Vellam's. Early in the operation, Griff warned that the blockade was ineffective and that the Rebels were steadily building up their fleet, advocating a decisive strike before the balance shifted to their favor. Vader, however, was too preoccupied with a scheme involving a [[Obi-Wan Kenobi impersonator|fake Obi-Wan Kenobi]] to engage in such an operation at the time, and Griff, stretched thin, watched his numerical superiority dwindle.

When the Rebels later mounted their final escape attempt, Vader once again pursued his own agenda, this time to leave a portion of the blockade deliberately weakened, allowing the Rebels to escape so that he could he lure them into a trap, again not bothering to inform Griff. Instead, the Admiral spotted the flaw by himself, sending three [[Imperial-class Star Destroyer/Legends|''Imperial''-class Star Destroyers]] to reinforce the breach and taking personal command of this force. The Rebels, led by Luke Skywalker, managed to defeat Griff's fighters and escaped past his positions at the [[Evacuation of Yavin|climax of the siege]]. He then opted for a gamble and ordered an immediate [[Hyperspace/Legends|hyperspace]] leap after the fleeing enemy.

[[File:GriffMeetsExecutor-CSW.png|thumb|250px|Griff's demise]]
With all the required information, the plan may well have worked. As it was, however, he brought his fleet out of hyperspace too close to Vader's [[Flagship/Legends|flagship]], the [[Executor/Legends|''Executor'']], which had secretly been waiting for the Rebels at this precise spot, and the ships collided. Griff was killed, and the three [[Star Destroyer/Legends|Star Destroyers]] that collided with the ''Executor'' were destroyed by the impact; the ''Executor'' lost its shields but suffered no major structural damage. It was, however, delayed long enough to allow the Rebels to escape.

==Personality and traits==
Griff was an ambitious man with few moral scruples, always ready to take advantage of the mistakes of others. He was also more than a little vain, wearing an expensive fur-brimmed coat, in addition to his standard service uniform. However, he was a competent, albeit at times somewhat brash, naval commander, and an accomplished agent with a working knowledge of ground combat tactics, making up for some of his other character flaws. To ensure a successful career, Griff "worked in [Vader's] shadow" and acted out his will. Though he proved himself a valuable subordinate and even fawned on him, the Admiral eventually grew weary of the Dark Lord's choices in command and made his own, ultimately fatal, gamble for glory. 

==Behind the scenes==
In the [[Star Wars (comic strip)|''Star Wars'' comic strip]] series in which he appears, Griff wears a nonstandard [[Rank insignia plaque/Legends|rank insignia]] that's all-red in the ''[[Classic Star Wars]]'' colorized reprintings rather than a standard admiral's badge.

